<br>
Having a guild have to wait a full cycle is unfair to the guilds who are trying to get on and will be slowing them down.  The guild trying to get onto a rotation is spending guild resources and people's playing time.  Both of which can be used for something else (another rotation, exp, whatever).  That is enough of the price to pay for an attempt.  <br>
<br>
Also, something very important to keep in mind.  Currently the rotation is 4 guilds, what happens when more and more get onto the rotation?  I propose that instead of having to change the rules down the line, you make one rule now that will hold no matter now many guilds are on the rotation.  Guilds trying to get onto rotation can try every other spawn, or have to wait 2 spawns between tries.  Either one will hold over time. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nyca>Nyca</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Singing Goddess</span><br>  Posts: 1323<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(12/20/02 1:05:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=410.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/slllyonec/EZemo/LeahHarp2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AoW and the Guild Rep forum</span><hr size=1> The Etiquette has been amended to add:<br>
