<br>
<br>
You can't call AoW a race.  Until the Statue guild takes down Statue, no one can do AoW.  It's fairly rude to have your guild waiting in the wings causing the Statue guild lag, not to mention a waste of the AoW guild's time (in reference to your point about wasting time &quot;racing&quot; to AoW).  At no time should a guild not on rotation see, and waste, more AoW's than a guild who is on rotation.  Every person that attempts and fails is depriving another guilld (and the server) of AoW loot.  Every guild that tries and fails on AoW removes one more AoW that would put us closer to leaving the rotation, thus slowing us down.  It's about give and take.<br>
<br>
Waiting for your Statue turn, I have sympathy and can see a reason for change.  However, watching FK, VoF, and any other guild down the line, get 2-3 shots to each of NB's shots hardly seems like a rotation to me.  Rotations are about sharing content between those who can kill, not those who are trying to.  While I understand your desire to progress, and your confidence in your guild's ability to kill AoW with &quot;one more shot&quot;, it isn't proven and can't be taken as fact.  The current AoW rotation guilds can point to a dead AoW (or more) and show why they shouldn't have to watch AoWs wasted excessively (every or every other AoW).  I see nothing wrong with you taking a shot, but then let all other guilds on the AoW rotation take their fair shot, which they earned.  They shouldn't have to be continually pushed off while you work out the kinks. <p>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.noble-blade.net&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://www.noble-blade.net/images/ezboard/sig-small.gif&quot; align=&quot;left&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Karadin Firethorne&lt;br&gt;Assassin of The Rathe&lt;br&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.noble-blade.net&quot;&gt;Noble Blade&lt;/a&gt; <br>
